testrunner is a ruby gem to run cppunit-tests within a workspace.
cppunit-tests must be already compiled,- output is written to .testrunner metafolder.

usage: testrunner <workspace> [options ...]

testrunner will call the unit-tests with command: some-test.exe -xml=cppunit.xml > cppunit.log
and copy cppunit.log & cppunit.xml to the metafolder if generated

if xml-output is generated test-results will be parsed 
within cppunit.xml by below format:

<TestRun>
...
  <Statistics>
    <Tests>2</Tests>
    <FailuresTotal>1</FailuresTotal>
    <Errors>0</Errors>
    <Failures>1</Failures>
  </Statistics>
</TestRun>

if no xml-output is generated test-results will be parsed 
by "!!!FAILURES!!!" pattern within cppunit.log
